    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>remaining garam masala</strong>, <strong>remaining curry powder </strong>and<strong> tomato paste</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[195ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and your <strong>baked beans </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 4-5 min or until the sauce has thickened</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
